---
import BlogArticleShell from '../../../components/BlogArticleShell.astro';

export const prerender = true;

const canonicalPath = '/blog/mulebuy-weidian';
const publishedISO = '2026-05-04';
---

<BlogArticleShell
  title="Weidian permalinks agents can digest | mulebuyai.com"
  description="Album drift and mobile hops break Spreadsheet discipline fast. Habits for capturing SKU-grade URLs before Mulebuy domestic pulls."
  canonicalPath={canonicalPath}
  headline="Weidian permalinks for Mulebuy intake"
  publishedISO={publishedISO}
  displayDate="4 May 2026"
>
  <p class="blog-lede" slot="lede">
    Weidian behaves like a collage engine: albums reshape, share buttons mutate, and mobile wrappers hide variant IDs. Spreadsheet browse helps, yet <strong>your clipboard still owes Mulebuy a reload-stable listing URL</strong>.
  </p>

  <h2>Preferred capture order</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>Open the SKU-level detail chrome—not just storefront grids.</li>
    <li>Select colour/size toggles before copying.</li>
    <li>Paste into a blank tab; confirm the variant persists.</li>
    <li>Only then feed Mulebuy’s intake.</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>Album drift checklist</h2>
  <p>
    If thumbnails update overnight, assume seller pivoted inventory. Reconcile Discord chatter with the live listing before funding—batch nostalgia misleads everyone.
  </p>
</BlogArticleShell>
